	(47,1,'2010-07-07 03:42:26','2010-07-07 03:42:26','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/13-The-Devil-The-Bottle-And-Me.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nOh, my God, where have you gone?\r\nIt\'s just the Devil, the bottle, and me\r\nAnd he filled my glass with a sinful past\r\nAnd it\'s about time for a drink\r\n\r\nAnd it\'s not that I don\'t want to try\r\nBut together they\'re so convincing\r\n\r\nOh angel, who\'s been through hell\r\nThere\'s a shoulder in need of your help\r\nCause all that\'s here to have my ear\r\nAre the Devilish words to myself\r\n\r\nAnd it\'s not that I believe the lies\r\nBut it\'s hard to hear anything else\r\n\r\nOh my faith, who\'s left to blame\r\nMy friends are all calling for truth\r\nSo I\'ll defer to Lucifer\r\nFor all the bad things that I do\r\n\r\nBut it\'s not that I \r\nDon\'t want him to die...\r\n\r\nBut you can\'t kill the Devil,\r\nNo you can\'t kill the Devil,\r\nNo you can\'t kill the Devil,\r\nWithout killing me too','The Devil, The Bottle and Me','','publish','open','open','','the-devil-the-bottle-and-me','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=47',13,'song','',0),
	(46,1,'2010-07-07 03:40:32','2010-07-07 03:40:32','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/12-Woman.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nI feel superficial thinking I could have you when\r\nYou\'ve been so goddamn noncommittal on the basis of just friends\r\nAnd I\'ve got nothing to compare it to except what we were back then\r\nAnd I find no comfort in the knowledge of how this has to end\r\n\r\nI\'ve been on the road for ninety days and ninety nights\r\nAnd I\'ve grown tired of leaving messages on all your busy lines\r\nSo I\'ve been dinking me straight whiskey, three bottles of Ten High\r\nWith a barely legal peddler of pills that make me right\r\n\r\nChorus:\r\nWoman\r\nWhy\'d you find me it\'s been so long\r\nDid you really think I\'d hold on\r\nWhen being fucked is just like going home\r\n\r\nSave your good intentions for the horse you rode in on \r\nAnd your charitable lessons as if there was right or wrong\r\nThere\'s only my accountability for things that we both done\r\nAnd this unstable relationship of my hand and this gun\r\n\r\nAnd I\'m brushing past the trigger who\'s as happy as could be\r\nAs I caress it with my finger like the was you caressed me\r\nAnd I finally found the answer to erase this memory\r\nBut I\'ve been dead a thousand times before and somehow I still breathe\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nAre you reaching? Are you reaching again?\r\nI know I am... I\'m sick of trying\r\n\r\nAre you happy? Are you happy with him?\r\nTell me softly so it can kill me\r\nAnd I can put these silly things away ','Woman','','publish','open','open','','woman','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=46',12,'song','',0),
	(45,1,'2010-07-07 03:38:10','2010-07-07 03:38:10','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/11-The-Song-That-Says-Goodbye.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nMaybe when you hate me you\'ll hear this song\r\nCause I\'ve been thinking lately that I\'ve been wrong\r\n\r\nDo you feel? Cause I feel like no one\r\nAnd maybe I\'m just been crazy all along\r\n\r\nChorus:\r\nI know I made you laugh, I\'m sure I mad you cry\r\nWe should just accept that I\'m no nice guy\r\n\r\nAnd I\'m sure your successor will get hurt too\r\nThe consommate professor of nothing new\r\n\r\nAnd I\'ll need, and she\'ll need like I do\r\nBut I\'ll put on the pressure to see it thru\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nOh baby it\'s Saturday night\r\nLet\'s go out, let\'s go make it right\r\n\r\nOh baby, but let\'s be warned\r\nThat nothing hurts better then when we are together Sunday morn\'\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nI have trouble looking back\r\nAnd I don\'t ask why\r\nWhat did we come together just to live, just to love, just to die\r\nI don\'t wanna die\r\n\r\nI apologize for being late\r\nIt\'s no way to start a date\r\nBut I think I should confess, this is me trying my best\r\nSo the beer and compliments are on me\r\n\r\nYou keep laughing at my clothes\r\nYou\'ve never seen so many holes\r\nBut you say you like my face, it ain\'t easy to mistake\r\nAnd you know how time erases memories\r\n\r\nAnd I live around the block next to old St. Peter\'s\r\nEveryday I get to walk through all sorts of believers\r\nWe can go there if you like\r\nMaybe you can stay the night, or month, or year\r\n\r\nI know it\'s forward, I\'ll go slower if it\'s weird\r\nWe\'re just so near... let\'s get out of here\r\n\r\nI kept on accusing everyone else\r\nFor these consistent bruises I gave myself\r\nIs it real when you realize no wealth?\r\nAnd you were best off losing with someone else','The Song That Says Goodbye','','publish','open','open','','the-song-that-says-goodbye','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=45',11,'song','',0),
	(44,1,'2010-07-07 03:27:46','2010-07-07 03:27:46','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/10-We-Make-Great-Enemies-Reprise.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nI sincerely hope that you are better\r\nBeing things that I\'m not\r\n\r\nSeeing you here where we had met her\r\nShows me all that I\'ve lost\r\n\r\nChorus:\r\nBut I never thought we\'d go this far\r\nWe were so quick to tear each other apart\r\nI guess I always knew you\'d be\r\nMy great enemy\r\n\r\nI know the crosses that you bare\r\nI\'ll be first to admit\r\n\r\nI\'m becoming more aware\r\nOf the things that I did\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nTook time to get fucked up before every show\r\nTook time to piss off everyone I know\r\nNow my reputations done\r\nWrote down every train I wrecked and every good thing that I stopped\r\nAnd I sing them every night but the only thing they want \r\nIs that repetitious song\r\nSo they can sing along\r\nAnd go home\r\n\r\nI\'d like to think that I could change\r\nBut I probably won\'t\r\nI know it sounds so deranged\r\nBut at least it\'s my own\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nSo alright\r\nGoodnight','We Make Great Enemies (Reprise)','','publish','open','open','','we-make-great-enemies-reprise','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=44',10,'song','',0),
	(43,1,'2010-07-07 03:26:11','2010-07-07 03:26:11','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/09-Planned-Attack.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nAnd I\'ve got myself prepared for battle\r\nAligned my chest with all my medals\r\nAnd got my soldiers ready for a fight\r\n\r\nAnd I\'ve built myself these war machines\r\nTo watch over what\'s left of me\r\nAnd instructed all of them to shoot on sight\r\n\r\nAs I mentioned in my declaration\r\nThere will be no negotiation\r\nThis is not something simply to avoid\r\n\r\nAnd if I see just one white flag raised\r\nI won\'t back down or disengage\r\nI\'ll just press on till everything\'s destroyed\r\n\r\nChorus:\r\n\'Cause if all is fair in love and war\r\nThen I\'ll have what\'s mine with brutal force\r\nAnd I\'ll change the world and settle scores\r\nAnd I\'ll get her back with my planned attack\r\n\r\nShe\'ll bunker down as if it\'s Troy\r\nShe\'ll seek protection from her boy\r\nBut some princes were never meant to rule\r\n\r\nAnd the only thing he can become\r\nIs a fortified Army of One \r\nWith a mouth built to remove the doubt in fools\r\n\r\nBut if our paths should cross tonight\r\nA chance I\'ll give before I strike\r\nTo wash the blood collected on their hands\r\n\r\nBut if she refuses to concede \r\nMy warriors await my lead\r\nTo take control of everything they can\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nI read my epitaph\r\nIt\'s much worse than I had thought \r\n\r\nWhen my time comes to pass\r\nI\'m killed by bullets my men shot\r\n\r\nIt seems my new philosophy\r\nIs what caused the mutiny\r\nI stood alone\r\n\r\nDespite what critics say\r\nI believe it\'s not my fault\r\n\r\nI\'ve been kept at bay\r\nAnd what you hear is the result\r\n\r\nIt seems these old fatalities\r\nCame with the melodies\r\nI stand alone\r\n\r\nWith the line they thought to draw\r\nAnd stand over as if it\'s law\r\nWill only tempt me further to advance\r\n\r\nWhile on their side of the white sand\r\nThe soapbox upon which they stand\r\nHelps them to bastardize my valiant stance\r\n\r\nBut Geneva has no jurisdiction\r\nWhich means there will be no conviction\r\nFor crimes made both in war and in passion\r\n\r\nIf I could finally have it all\r\nTheir whole empire soon will fall\r\nThen I will be the one who finally won\r\n\r\nChorus','Planned Attack','','publish','open','open','','planned-attack','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=43',9,'song','',0),
	(41,1,'2010-07-07 03:23:14','2010-07-07 03:23:14','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/08-The-Sound.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nI\'ve been petrified of nothing\r\nAnd it grows closer everyday\r\nI keep believing I found something\r\nThen it just simply goes away\r\n\r\nChorus:\r\nThis is the sound of me losing\r\nI\'ve vilified my hands so they don\'t talk\r\nAnd every metaphor I\'m using\r\nWon\'t help you understand the roads I walk\r\n\r\nI\'ve been paralyzed with worry\r\nI only have enough to raise a glass\r\nI\'ve lost the will to write I\'m sorry\r\nI guess we\'ll see how long your patience last\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nI don\'t want to come across as boring\r\nWith some sort of cliche point of view\r\nMaybe I\'ll just write about misfortune\r\nAnd we can pretend it\'s something new\r\n\r\nI don\'t want to die and be forgotten\r\nI don\'t want to live and not be heard\r\nI don\'t want to be inside some poorly written waste\r\nMaybe if I told you what I\'ve wanted\r\nMaybe if you listened to the words\r\nMaybe we could wipe these sad expressions off our face','The Sound','','publish','open','open','','the-sound','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=41',8,'song','',0),
	(40,1,'2010-07-07 03:20:43','2010-07-07 03:20:43','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/07-Dont-Want-Nothin.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nDon\'t call me superstitious when I catch you watching her\r\nWith your dirty little secrets of the places that you were\r\nAnd you can play it cool\r\nOr act the fool\r\nIt all looks well rehearsed\r\nYou\'ve been talking me in circles, as if somehow I\'ve not heard\r\n\r\nChorus:\r\nSo I... yeah I... yeah I... don\'t want nothin\'\r\nAnd I... yeah I... yeah I... don\'t want nothin\' from you\r\n\r\nDon\'t call it paranoia that whole thing has gotten old\r\nI know you talk about me when I go out on the road\r\nAnd it ain\'t the wine\r\nOr in my mind\r\nOr the fact that I\'m so stoned\r\nYou both been fucking with me and its time to let you know\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nYou best now pay attention cause I\'ll only say this once\r\nDon\'t think I\'m leavin, don\'t think I\'m giving up\r\nAnd I just shout\r\nAnd get kicked out\r\nBut I\'ll just wait out front\r\nSo if you think that it\'s over... (let me tell you something) it\'s just begun\r\n\r\nChorus','Don\'t Want Nothin\'','','publish','open','open','','dont-want-nothin','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=40',7,'song','',0),
	(39,1,'2010-07-07 03:17:02','2010-07-07 03:17:02','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/06-Better-Me.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nHow gracious of you to finally come home\r\nI\'m wasted, and you won\'t pick up your phone\r\nI know it\'s mean, but I thought that tonight\r\nCould stay between the likes of you and I \r\n\r\nChorus:\r\nDon\'t try to better me\r\nAs if I\'m unaware of who you are\r\nYou can\'t change a memory\r\nJust because you\'ve had a change of heart\r\nI\'ve got a remedy, let\'s lock ourselves inside and go to far\r\nLike from the start\r\n\r\nI\'m curious where is it that you\'ve been\r\nYour marvaleous attire says with him\r\nBut don\'t you fuss there\'s nothing to regret\r\nI bought enough for us both to forget\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nI thought that you cared about me\r\nThat you couldn\'t live without me\r\nBut I see that simply isn\'t true\r\n\r\nI don\'t care about the neighbors\r\nThis isn\'t some ridiculous behavior\r\nI know what you\'ve done and so do you\r\n\r\nI don\'t give a damn who\'s looking\r\nI hope they here me all the way in Brooklyn\r\nSo he knows exactly where I\'m going to\r\n\r\nUnless there\'s something else you\'d rather do\r\n\r\nMy time machine is broke, so let\'s pretend\r\nThat we\'re both clean, and this is how we met\r\nAnd we\'d be great cause I learned to say no\r\nIt\'s not too late, stop saying I should go\r\n\r\nChorus','Better Me','','publish','open','open','','better-me','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=39',6,'song','',0),
	(38,1,'2010-07-07 03:11:35','2010-07-07 03:11:35','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/05-Notes-And-Measures.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nThose corner kids don\'t have a clue\r\nThey\'re still waiting to be rescued\r\nThey stay and sway, but I know better\r\n\r\nThis is where I used to roam\r\nI knew a girl who would wear headphones\r\nin bed instead of letting me get her\r\n\r\nChorus:\r\nWhere a crook would find a cave\r\nCounting trinkets he acquired\r\nAnd a person could be saved before noon\r\nWhere I would hold a flame\r\nTo what fueled them to inspire\r\nEvery light a burning fire from their room\r\n\r\nThat\'s our names in the cement\r\nWe used the sidewalk as our canvas\r\nTo show if we go, something\'s forever\r\n\r\nThere\'s people living in these trees\r\nSome can go a hundred stories\r\nBut somehow, there\'s no sound, just doors and letters\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nThey act like it\'s their right\r\nThey make it seem as if we\'ve stolen\r\nIn the dead of night we\'re shown the street\r\nThey paint the sticks and stones\r\nThey make the roads all clean and golden\r\nThey buried broken bones beneath their feet\r\n\r\nMost who started here have left\r\nIt\'s all in the name of progress\r\nBut now this whole crowd is just big spenders\r\n\r\nThis neighborhood was filled with words\r\nNow everyone here speaks in numbers\r\nSo I just reply in notes and measures\r\n\r\nChorus','Notes and Measures','','publish','open','open','','notes-and-measures','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=38',5,'song','',0),
	(37,1,'2010-07-07 02:59:11','2010-07-07 02:59:11','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/04-Lick-The-Thumb-Turn-The-Page.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nWe\'re much better when we drink\r\nWe\'re much better then you think\r\n\r\nThese kind of places have no list\r\nIf you want I\'ll pay for it\r\n\r\nMy drummer\'s friend\'s in A&R\r\nHe seems to think we could go far\r\n\r\nIt\'s much harder than it sounds\r\nBeing no one in this town\r\n\r\nChorus:\r\nCan you hear it?\r\nCan you see it?\r\nCause I keep dreaming and I\'ve got no feeling left inside\r\nAll I need is some semblance of me to fill the stage\r\nLick the thumb and turn the page\r\n\r\nIt gets lonelier each day\r\nWhen you\'re half the moon away\r\n\r\nDid you get that magazine?\r\nThere\'s an article on me\r\n\r\nMy drummer\'s friend thinks we\'re a hit\r\nI seem to think he\'s full of shit\r\n\r\nIt\'s much harder than it sounds\r\nTo keep on losing to be found\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nSympathetic balladeer\r\nPays much better than I feared\r\nAnd I\'ll waste it all away\r\nAnd I\'ll waste it all away\r\nAnd I\'ll waste it all away\r\n\r\nWe go out most every night\r\nCan\'t remember the daylight\r\n\r\nAll these evenings that I\'ve spent\r\nWith all these people I\'ll forget\r\n\r\nWe debuted at number nine\r\nLeft my drummer\'s friend behind\r\n\r\nIt\'s much harder than it sounds\r\nBeing no one in this town\r\n\r\nIt\'s much harder than it sounds\r\nBeing no one in this town','Lick the Thumb, Turn the Page','','publish','open','open','','lick-the-thumb-turn-the-page','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=37',4,'song','',0),
	(36,1,'2010-07-07 02:57:07','2010-07-07 02:57:07','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/03-Her-Name-Is-Aylene.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nThey told me I should look more like a movie \r\nNobody listens to stories, four minutes is much too long\r\n\r\nSo I worked out, thought of the things that I write about\r\nForgot all my worries for right now, sat down and wrote this song\r\n\r\nAnd it goes like...\r\n\r\nChorus:\r\nWho\'s the prettiest girl?\r\nWho\'s the prettiest girl?\r\nThe prettiest girl I know...\r\nI know... Her name is Aylene\r\n\r\nSo I went back thinking that I would get laughed at\r\nThey said \"son, I think we here one track that we can finally use\"\r\n\r\nAnd by morning, I finished all the recording\r\nI know that it sounds kind of corny, but I named it after you\r\n\r\nAnd it goes like...\r\n\r\nChorus','Her Name is Aylene','','publish','open','open','','her-name-is-aylene','','','2014-09-08 22:03:56','2014-09-09 02:03:56','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=36',3,'song','',0),
	(35,1,'2010-07-07 02:53:46','2010-07-07 02:53:46','[audio src=\"http://goodbyepicasso.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/02-Silhouettes.mp3\"]\r\n\r\nI am watching silhouettes\r\nI am talking with nothing but my ill intent to know\r\nHow far you want to go\r\n\r\nYou are holding cheap champagne\r\nYou are toasting every single face and name, and oh...\r\nHere\'s one for the show\r\n\r\nYou look so beautiful\r\nYou\'re losing your control\r\n\r\nChorus:\r\nWe may climb up the mountain,  we may get involved\r\nBut you prefer it on the bottom where nothing gets resolved\r\n\r\nYou\'re discussing waitressing\r\nYou\'re entrusting, all the world with drunken things supposed\r\nLike how you\'ll make it home\r\n\r\nYou refer to me as Rose\r\nCause names are seldom known\r\n\r\nChorus\r\n\r\nGirl you look so lovely\r\nGirl you look so lovely\r\nYeah you do\r\n\r\nI can make you happy\r\nI can make you happy\r\nGirl it\'s true\r\n\r\nI\'ll throw nickels at the poor and you\'ll never know they\'re wooden\r\nI will walk you to your door, so I can get my foot inside\r\nI know a lullaby\r\n\r\nI\'m singing,\r\nIf you\'re dreaming, keep believing in me\r\nAll I\'ll offer, is less time for us to suffer\r\n','Silhouettes','','publish','open','open','','silhouettes','','','2014-09-08 22:03:57','2014-09-09 02:03:57','',0,'http://goodbyepicasso.com/?post_type=song&#038;p=35',2,'song','',1),
